node.title: Same weird family. New weird problems. The Umbrella Academy Returns July 31

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gerard Way on June 09, 2021.

node.text: The 12th and final issue of Far Sector is out now! You won’t want to miss the finale of this epic story. And not only is today the final chapter of the book, but it was nominated today for an Eisner Award for Best Limited Series. I’m so happy for this team— N.K. Jemisin wrote it, Jamal Campbell (@pryce14) handled the art, colors, and covers, and Deron Bennette (@andworlddesign) took care of the lettering. They put everything they had into it, and it was truly a pleasure to watch this creative team craft this story for 12 issues. It was an honor to be able to put this out on Young Animal. Go check it out, and the collection of this series is coming soon.

node.text:
Jacob Raggio

September 30th, 1985 - March 19th, 2021 

Been trying to think of the best way to put it into words, but this is a huge loss, for everyone whose life he touched, and of course for his family who loved him dearly. 

I’ll never forget the first time I met Jake. We were doing a couple of production days at the arena to get everything in order for the first big Black Parade tour with full production, so there were a lot of moving pieces. I remember our head carpenter Thor asking me to come back and take a look at something they were working on, which I believe was a facade of a traditional upright piano that the keyboards could sit in, painted black. It looked great. Next to Thor was this young fresh faced kid with a beard, who was the carpenter’s assistant. He introduced himself as Jake. Immediately you could feel his excitement, enthusiasm, and positivity. You could tell right away he was someone that wanted to be a part of something, wanted to go on that great big adventure that touring can be and see the world. He worked hard, and his enthusiasm never wavered, even when touring got difficult. He kept working his way up. Fast forward to Project Rev years later and he’s was now stage managing us, and before we went on, just like the tours before this, Jake would round everyone up for the high-five line and start getting everyone juiced. And he was so pure and sincere you couldn’t help get as excited as he was. He’d pace back and forth, saying “Get it, boys. Get it.”, and we did, and he was the first face you would see as you walked off stage and you could fee how proud he was every night, because a victory for us was a victory for everyone, him included. I will miss him so much. And it may have felt at first that the world was a little dimmer without his light, but his light is truly eternal and I’ll feel it every time I’m about to go on stage. Sending love and condolences to his family, he will be missed.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gerard Way on March 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'MIKEY SHAUN TOBY WAY SIMON CYPRESS ELECTRIO CENTURY ntury LCASINO RESORT'.

node.text:
Last week, my brother (in biology as well as rock) @mikeyway and co released not one, but two projects that have been in the works for some time. @ElectricCentury— a new graphic novel through @z2comics as well as a new record. ⠀
⠀
When Mikey and I were kids, we spent a lot of time in Atlantic City, walking the boardwalk and watching the lights. The memories, the feeling of that is something I feel when reading the book and seeing the art across the pages. It brings me back— I couldn’t be more proud of him and these releases. ⠀
⠀
@dvdebiak and Mikey did the album, @raytoro, along with some others, produced. It’s a great album. I think Little Things may be my favorite, has a cool vibe that takes me back to listening to Pulp. ⠀
⠀
My longtime Killjoys collaborator Shaun Simon wrote the book with Mikey, and Toby Cypress, @punkrockjazz, handled the art, which is stunning. Toby is actually one of my favorite artists, kinetic and expressive and impactful. The whole thing is a great experience, both the music and the graphic novel. Enjoy!

node.text: Tune in tomorrow evening (Tuesday, March 2nd) to see me speak about mental health at #UnwoundAndUnplugged at 5 pm PT/8 pm ET, presented by @soundmind_live and @nationaldayofunplugging. The virtual event will stream from my Facebook page and @soundmind_live's YouTube Channel. See you soon! #SoundMind

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gerard Way on February 24, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
Hey all, I’m a little late to the party because I’ve been spending so much time in the lab. My brother in rock @frankieromustdie put out an amazing EP with his band The Future Violents called Heaven Is A Place, This Is A Place and I love it. From the doom and groove of Sewer Wolf and Violence, to a badass REM cover, to the dreamy and powerful Record Ender, it’s a great EP and I found myself head banging along. It sounds tough and textured, and I love the nuanced and dynamic vocal performances. Check it out! Streaming & download link in bio.

Xo G.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gerard Way on February 23, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SOUND MIND PRESENTS UNWOUND & UNPLUGGED Mental Health Fostering Deeper Connection ABenefit Concert & Panel MARCH2 (5PT/8ET) soundmindlive.org GERARD WAY OF CHEMICAL ROMANCE You Tube Live LIVE'.

node.text: I'm excited to speak at #UnwoundAndUnplugged, presented by @soundmind_live and @nationaldayofunplugging, coming up on March 2nd! This virtual mental health concert and panel brings together myself, @julienrbaker and @deathbyromy to promote a community of support around experiences related to mental health, isolation and the healing power of creativity and connection. I know that it's a really tough time for everyone right now. Coming together as a community and speaking openly about mental health is more relevant than ever. The event takes place on Facebook at 5pm PT/ 8pm ET on March 2nd.
